# Plan: Discord Bot Web Dashboard

## Overview

A Next.js 16 (App Router, TypeScript) dashboard in a **separate GitHub repo** (e.g. `Discord-Bot-Dashboard`), deployed to Vercel for free. Uses Discord OAuth2 to log in, connects to the same MongoDB as the bot, and lets guild admins configure all 5 sections from a browser.

## Architecture

- **Repo:** New standalone repo — not a subdirectory of the bot repo
- **Framework:** Next.js 16.1.6 (App Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **Auth:** NextAuth v4.24.13 (stable, supports Next.js 16) with Discord provider (scopes: `identify guilds`)
- **Database:** Mongoose 8.14.3 connecting to the same MongoDB cluster
- **Validation:** Zod
- **Forms:** react-hook-form + @hookform/resolvers
- **Hosting:** Vercel (free tier, auto-deploys from GitHub)

